  "prompt": "What is the best pancake recipe that doesn't use baking powder?",
  "response": "Here's a simple pancake recipe without baking powder:\n\nIngredients:\n- 1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour\n- 3 1/2 teaspoons baking soda\n- 1 teaspoon salt\n- 1 tablespoon sugar\n- 1 1/4 cups milk\n- 1 egg\n- 3 tablespoons melted butter\n\nInstructions:\n1. Mix dry ingredients in a bowl\n2. Whisk milk, egg, and melted butter in another bowl\n3. Combine wet and dry ingredients, mixing until just combined (some lumps are okay)\n4. Let batter rest for 5-10 minutes\n5. Heat a lightly greased skillet or griddle\n6. Pour 1/4 cup batter for each pancake\n7. Cook until bubbles form on top, then flip and cook other side\n8. Serve warm with butter and syrup\n\nNote: Baking soda is used instead of baking powder. The recipe works because the acid in milk reacts with the baking soda to help the pancakes rise and become fluffy.\n\nTips:\n- Don't overmix the batter\n- Let batter rest to allow baking soda to activate\n- Use medium heat to prevent burning",
